<db:section xml:id="isParameterSupported">
<db:title>[pure virtual] bool QCameraImageProcessingControl::isParameterSupported(QCameraImageProcessingControl::ProcessingParameter <db:emphasis>parameter</db:emphasis>) const</db:title>
<db:para>Returns true if the camera supports adjusting image processing <db:code role="parameter">parameter</db:code>.</db:para>
<db:para>Usually the supported setting is static, but some parameters may not be available depending on other camera settings, like presets. In such case the currently supported parameters should be returned.</db:para>
</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="isParameterValueSupported">
<db:title>[pure virtual] bool QCameraImageProcessingControl::isParameterValueSupported(QCameraImageProcessingControl::ProcessingParameter <db:emphasis>parameter</db:emphasis>, const QVariant &amp;<db:emphasis>value</db:emphasis>) const</db:title>
<db:para>Returns true if the camera supports setting the image processing <db:code role="parameter">parameter</db:code> <db:code role="parameter">value</db:code>.</db:para>
<db:para>It's used only for parameters with a limited set of values, like <db:link xlink:href="qcameraimageprocessingcontrol.xml#ProcessingParameter-enum">WhiteBalancePreset</db:link>.</db:para>
</db:section>
